data.title: First Automated Luggage Storage Network in Europe - Smart Lockers Easy Life
data.meta_description: Automated smart lockers network in Europe. Reservation online / onsite up to 3 locker sizes. We are open 365 days. The exact location is given in advance. Don’t pay per item, save money & rent a locker with Stow Your Bags! Safe, smart & insured!
data.text:
11/05/2024 - John S

"The initial instructions were easy to follow. However, they said I would receive a text and/or email with a retrieval code which I never received (I also had no cell service on Italy, so I had to find a place with WiFi to check), so I had to make sure we came back early enough to use the original code and make sure we could still retrieve our bags. This, of course, made it impossible to officially close out the rental until I finally got an email to do so from Stowyourbags.com several hours later. On top of that, we found a dead mouse in the back of the locker after retrieving our bags!"

30/04/2024 - Martin Alford

"Very easy to book online. I very much appreciated the detailed directions to the location of the facility, as without knowing to look out for the 'Posta' sign it would have been easy to miss the narrow alley. Once there, using the machine was easy and the bags were put away in no time. I'd ordered the large size for two large aircraft cabin bags plus a rucksack and there was plenty of spare room, so the lockers are of a generous size. It's a shame there's no room in the facility for a table on which to move things into/out of bags you're leaving or taking with you - there were people kneeling on the floor doing this. But I guess installing a working surface in the space available would take up too much room. I am very impressed with Stow Your Bags, and will certainly use the service again. It's not expensive and saves having to lug cases around to everyone's irritation if you find yourself on an evening flight with time to kill in the city. Well done for spotting a need and filling it!"

21/04/2024 - ERIC NIPPARD

"The process of using the storage unit was easy and very smooth. Instructions are provided at the kiosk that allow swift access to the bins. However, the sizing instructions are a touch misleading in that they indicate that a standard bin will hold two standard sized suitcases. On that recommendation, I ordered a standard bin to store two bags. However, the bin was barely big enough to hold a single, standard sized suitcase. It had room to store two of what would be classed as carry on sized bags, and NOT standard sized bags. I had to purchase a second bin, on site, in order to store the second bag. This would have been a touch tricky should all the bins have been booked! The company needs to adjust their sizing chart to reflect the reality of what can be stored."

17/04/2024 - Krista L

"Reserving and using the lockers could not have been easier! Some people have complained about the location being difficult to find, but if you map it on Google, it takes you right there. We had one mid-size checked suitcase, 4 carry-on sized suitcases (with a couple expanded) and 2 backpacks. We reserved 3 max sized lockers to ensure we had enough room and everything fit easily, with room to spare. I highly recommend reserving space ahead of time. As we were leaving, a large crowd of people were arriving. I'm not sure if they had locker space reserved but there aren't a ton of lockers so I'd be worried about finding space if I were to just show up without a reservation."

07/04/2024 - XIAO CHEN

"Dear Sir/Madam, I hope this email finds you well. I recently utilized your luggage storage service during my visit to Rome on April 3rd. However, upon reviewing my payment records, I noticed that I was inadvertently charged twice for the service on the same date. The duplicate charge amounted to 8.99 euros. I could like to give the payment records for you if you give me the e-mail address. I kindly request your prompt assistance in rectifying this oversight by issuing a refund for the duplicate fee. I would appreciate it if the refund could be processed back to the original payment method used for the transaction. Should you require any further information or clarification regarding this matter, please do not hesitate to contact me via email at this address. Thank you for your attention to this matter. I look forward to receiving confirmation of the refund and sincerely appreciate your prompt resolution of this issue. Warm regards, Xiao chen"

28/03/2024 - JP

"Booked in advance and used twice. Couldn't be simpler really - very well designed system. You enter your booking code on the screen and the locker number allocated to you is displayed on the screen. The lockers are clearly numbered and the door of the locker matching the screen number will pop open ready for you to use. Within the time booked you can open and close the locker as many times as you like - just use the screen to re-key in your code to open it. Don't accidentally close the locker with your locker code details inside!!! If you don't need all your remaining time you can opt to close the locker and finish your period - I assume this is to free up the locker for someone else to use. Booking ahead seems like a good idea - keying in a code is much simpler and quicker than hoping there is a free locker available and paying for time . It also leaves no doubt whether or not a locker will be available when needed. We found the locker room varied greatly in terms of how busy it was. Sometimes it was virtually empty but other times it was very busy. The busy times were largely due to people trying to find a luggage storage locker on an ad-hoc basis and then pay with cards etc. The system was very simple to book and use, reasonably priced as well, so will definitely use again."

10/03/2024 - Nadine Stewart

"I’ve used a couple of luggage storage facilities in other cities (Paris, Seville) but neither were as smooth, easy and efficient as this place! It worked so well. You receive the info you need via text & email. You go there (it’s very close to the train station) and even though there is no human being located there, the onscreen instructions are so very clear and easy to understand, you don’t really need to ask a human being anything (I hate to say that, as I do worry technology is making human beings obsolete but it’s true!) Even when you do have an issue, all you do is press the button above the screen and there’s a human being for you to immediately talk to. Unfortunately, even though I’d measured my suitcase before leaving home, it turned out I couldn’t fit it into the standard locker I had paid for. I spoke to someone via that button and she explained I’d have to make a new reservation for a maxi locker instead but I would be refunded the amount I paid for the previous locker. I purchased and used a larger locker & I also received an email confirming the refund in writing. My issue was dealt with quickly and all went well overall. I’d highly recommend using this very convenient luggage storage option."

12/01/2024 - Gilli Hanna

"Super offering, easy to use, really close to the Ferrovia. The remote human service was very helpful as I had booked storage for the wrong date. I was rebooked on the correct date with no problem. Coming out of the railway station to the wonderful view ahead of one, it could be easy to miss the access ramp. It's to the right of the steps at the exit of the station. Once down the ramp it's all level to Stow Your Bags. Look for a little yellow Poste sign down an alley on your right. You will see the Poste at the bottom of the alley and SYB is hidden just to the right. Thank you very much!"

03/12/2023 - Lady G

"We went to Venice for a day on 11/29, and we needed a place to stow our bags while we walked around before heading to Milan, and Stow Your Bags was perfect! The place was super easy to find, and just within a couple of minutes walk from the Santa Lucia Station. The place felt secured, and it had a camera inside so that made me feel even better. Price was very reasonable, and the space was enough. I rented the smaller locker, and I was able to fit a backpack, a carry on suitcase, and a duffel bag. I should’ve rented the bigger locker to have more space in between the bags, but like I said before, everything fit perfectly. I definitely recommend this place. Only word of advice would be to rent a bigger locker if you are carrying more than 2 bags."

20/11/2023 - Ellisa

"It saved our shoulders and allowed us some sightseeing on our last day in Rome. Felt fairly safe to leave our bags there. It was not far from the train station, and near quaint cafes. It was fairly clean - a quick wipe down with a Wet-wipe was sufficient for me. Unfortunately the code to retrieve our bags was sent via email, and my data did not cooperate - we had a few stressful minutes waiting for the email to come through so we could get our bags back out before our train left. It would've been more conveniently located in the train station or right across the street, but then we wouldn't have stopped at one of those cafes."

25/10/2023 - Lisa Westbrook

"Used the location by Atocha train station in Madrid. Perfect - easy to find just two mins away from the station. Easy instructions to follow upon arrival. We had to reopen locker before the session was ended but simple with extra instructions. All automated. Seamless and just what we needed. I don't know how much the cost compares with other luggage storage facilities in the City as this is the first time we have used this type of storage (always been at a hotel). We paid 15 Euro for one day as had an evening flight and needed more than 6 hours storage. You can pay by the hour if only required for a short period of time. Would definitely use again. Many thanks."

22/10/2023 - Phyllis Priess

"Stow Your Bags was recommended to us by our Air BnB host. We reserved 2 units online in advance using their easy to follow instructions. When we arrived we discovered one of the units was not large enough so we were able to rent a second larger unit. When we retrieved our luggage at the end of the rental period, we did not think to follow the check out procedure for the smaller unit we had not actually used. The next day we got an email saying our rental of that unit was still running. When we explained the situation, we were very kindly not charged for the extra time, and in fact, we were reimbursed for the pre-booked rental of the smaller unit since we had not ended up using it. Would highly recommend this business."

20/10/2023 - PAULINE

"These are 100 percent automated storage lockers and were simple to use. Just 2 comments to be aware of. 1. They are priced by the size of the locker (small and large) and by the duration of proposed usage. So, the 'from price' quoted on the website is probably for a small locker for 30 mins I presume. The large locker was 17.50 EUR for 6 hours for us. 2. It would be helpful if one could see how many lockers were available before you start the 'check in' process on the screen. We wanted a large locker but when I tried to book, it said none were available. So I tried to choose 2 small lockers... but it would only let me select 1 small locker. I assumed that was all that was left ( All doors on lockers are closed so you have no idea if they are available or in use. ). I put a bag in the one locker I had then paid for and then the people in the queue behind me suddenly were also able to get one small locker. So I again returned to the screen to try and get a 2nd small locker. It then told me that none were available, but a LARGE locker was available! Someone else in the queue must have just returned and freed up a large locker! It being my only choice I then rented that one. So I ended up with a large and a small locker (paid for) when really I just needed one large one. So my only hint would be, if you arrive and the locker size that you need is not available as you make your request on the screen, ask if anyone in that queue/room is about to retrieve their luggage and free up a locker. If they are let them go ahead of you in the queue and allow you (being next in line) to then book that locker. Without asking it is not clear if people are there to book lockers or empty lockers and everyone needs to queue for the same single booking/release screen"

09/10/2023 - TWAN ACKERMANS

"Great experience. We booked a locker to safely store our bags while we were out exploring Genua. There are two sizes, regular and maxi. If you book on site, you can try the sizes to see what size best suits your needs before booking. You can book via the terminal on site. It was the easiest booking experience I have ever had for such a locker. It is available in multiple languages. After booking, your locker opens automatically. You receive an email immediately afterwards with the code you have to use to open your locker. You can open your locker during the booking period to get items in and out of your bags if necessary. The prices are very fair in my opinion. All in all a great experience, would definitely use again."

25/09/2023 - Noel Amador

"This was a great option. Very convenient and well located to the train station. It's nice to be able to leave your bags and get on with your day. I got the details well in advance after I pre-booked and the kiosk was fast and easy to use. It took less than 5 minutes to drop off bags. I would suggest adding a second kiosk since I had to wait 20 minutes to pick up my bags. I had pre-booked and was ready to go. I ended up having to wait after a family of 8 each wanted a locker and had not pre-booked. Two kiosk would have made it better, thankfully the system worked fast once the line cleared. Great option for travelers!"

19/07/2023 - Rickety

"We needed to safely stash our bags for a few hours at the end of our trip to Rome and discovered "StowYourBags" The locating and booking of a locker was simple and easy to understand. We received email and text confirmation with instructions almost immediately after paying. We found the lockers themselves to be smaller than we thought, although they seemed to be as described on the website. We booked a maxi which is about a little larger than a full sized hard cased suitcase, we also had a soft frameless rucsac type bag which we managed to squeeze into the remaining space - it was a struggle :-) Definitely worth booking in advance, we tried on the day to buy more space for the rucsac but nothing left so persevered with the one we booked. If in doubt book a larger space than you think - the price difference is negligible considering the alternative of lugging about baggage whilst enjoying the remaining hours of your trip. For the price, ease of use and peace of mind we would use them again."

21/06/2023 - Cin Tanaka

"Great service, we used it to store our luggage (1 small bag 2 backpacks). We used the maxi size locker and had plenty of space left. I would just suggest two improvements: 1. Having one machine for those who already have a reservation and one for those who are hiring the service on the spot to avoid long queues 2. Having a system that allows us to type our codes in a more secure way. The numbers are giant on the screen, so I felt a bit exposed. It would be nice to be able to type it on the card machine or to have a system like the ones bank use with two numbers shown in the button for selecting each digit (0 or 9, 4 or 6 etc.)"

28/03/2023 - AJO

"We were staying in an apartment in Valencia and had a late flight. Our host recommended this service and it was just the ticket. On the corner of a side street next to the train station (North) it was easy to find and just 2 mins from the Xativa metro station (line 3) which took us to the airport. We booked the service online the day before, picked the hours for drop off and pick up. The cost for the number of hours the service is being used is clearly shown. We were given a code by E Mail to put into the system when we arrived and it allocated / opened a locker for us. We put our two small cases in the locker (selected 'standard') and shut the locker. Spent the afternoon caseless enjoying our last few hours in this lovely city. When we picked our cases up we put the same code in the system and our locker opened. We found the service easy to use and value for money. Gracias StowYourBags."

05/11/2022 - julie rowland

"Great service and very convenient, which enabled us as a family to spend more time exploring Paris without carting our cases along with us. Even though the area is slightly seedy (not StowYourBags fault) I felt my belongings were safe whilst left in the locker for 6 hours (which I had pre-booked in the UK in case we turned up and it was full) I didn't realise this sort of service existed and will certainly use the facilities again when travelling in Europe. One slight panic moment was on closing the locker it informed me that within 5 minutes I would be sent an email with the release code. This didn't happen, but on arriving at back at StowYourBags my locker opened fine with the original code."

21/10/2022 - LAURA HENDERSON

"It was a short, easy walk from Milan Central Train Station. When I got to the address the door to enter wouldn't open so I figured it was out-of-business. While I was on my phone searching for an alternative someone came and went in another door to the right of the ones I tried. It would have been nice to have an arrow on the door that didn't open pointing to the one that did. Simple error on my part, but there are many weary travelers that may make the same mistake and give up. The process to choose and pay was clear and when you pay the locker pops open then you store your bags. You are then emailed a code to enter when you return, which opens the locker again. There is a choice of two options, in Italian, when you enter the code. You want the one on the right, which immediately opens your locker. Someone familiar with the system told me which one to press. I had a carry-on suitcase and a carry-on duffle/Sportif bag that was stuffed so I chose a Standard-sized locker which is supposed to hold two bags. I did have to really push on the flexible bag to close the door, so if you have two larger carry-ons, I'd suggest the larger size locker. I'd use this option again if the station didn't have storage. I did see one in the train station later, but don't know if bags are under surveillance. I liked the fact that my bags were actually locked up not out in the open."

08/10/2022 - Carlito

"Wasn't sure what to expect but the location was really easy to find and locker easy to use. There is a terminal screen at the far end of the small shop with lockers along the walls. You enter the email confirmation code which opens up a locker in the size ordered. Fit a standard carry-on bag with wheels plus a filled backpack in the standard size locker with room to spare. The location is behind Madrid Atocha station so a bit of a walk since most exits are from the other side of the station. But the location is easily accessible and seems safe. There is even a nice tavern, Sidreria La Posada, on the same street corner. We got a good late lunch there before getting our bags to catch an afternoon train to Barcelona.On return, we just entered the same confirmation code to open the locker. Really easy to use!"

08/07/2022 - Anna Jaeger

"The store was easy to find and easy to reserve online. My only wish is that there was a separate online-only keypad. When I arrived, the line was out the door. People were fumbling to order at the kiosk while I had to wait 20 minutes for my 10 second process of simply keying in my code and opening the lockers. There could also be a couple of improvements to the application. The lockers were all full and people were just standing around waiting. It would be helpful if they could see what rentals were due to expire so they could determine if it was worth waiting around for. Also, I paid for 3 hours but 30 minutes in I learned that I could check into my apartment. I would be great to be able to get somewhat of a refund for checking out early - it would have helped me out and it definitely made the customer waiting without a reservation happy - they immediately rented my lockers."

16/05/2022 - OLENA TARASYUK

"I was really happy to have found your service because I really needed to leave my bags to go to the event. It was very easy to use and self-explanatory. The only issue is that doors to the storage room closes between 23:00-07:00, so you have no access to your luggage. I needed to leave my things only for a few hours during the night and because of room being locked, I missed my morning train at 5 AM as I couldn't get my luggage out. My mistake, because 'opening time' was mentioned on the door, but I would never think that I wouldn't be able to get my things back when I needed to."

19/01/2022 - Mariani

"Actually it is easy to use and helpful but it will be better if we can choose the locker. I rent the big locker (maxi) because I had a big luggage and it was heavy enough. But when I finished the payment and the locker is opened, I surprised because I got the locker that is on top. I was very struggling to put my very big luggage inside and I must took out some of my stuffs from the luggage and put it aside so it became lighter a little bit. But it was still difficult to put it on top and I was alone at that time. Hope later the service will be better."

20/09/2021 - NELS from the US

"Make sure you have internet access before planning to use this service. Unlike some others I have used, this service does not provide a printout of the unlock code for your locker, it is instead emailed to you and texted to you. I had a European e-Sim card in my iPhone so I had data service and received the email. I never received the text message. Otherwise, the service was fine. They have one locker of each size with no door so that you can ensure your luggage will fit in one. The process is straightforward and offered in multiple languages. It is certainly better than hauling your baggage around Pisa with you if you are just there as a side trip."

16/11/2020 - ANNA KANIUK

"We had an awesome experience with Stow Your Bags in Venice. Our train arrived around 6am, and Stow Your Bags was open from 7am (much earlier than any other place we had researched). It was only a few minutes' walk from the train station to the locker area, and if you're looking for the "Poste Italiano" sign pointing down an alleyway, you'll find it easily. The long line was to the post office, not to the luggage place, so don't be fooled. There was nobody else in the luggage place. We had two large suitcases and two medium-sized backpacks; we ended up needing two normal-size lockers for this and paid 14.50 for 4 hours. Most people would probably have less luggage though and be able to get away with one normal or large size locker. Everything was easy to figure out on the touch screen machine. Make sure to keep your receipt and close the locker afterwards when you take your bags away. Super easy and hassle-free!"

02/02/2020 - DAVID BYRNE

"I made the mistake of not realising your lockers are designed only for cabin baggage - not for hold luggage, which was what I needed in order to avoid rolliong a heavy suitcase all the way from Pisa railway station to the Leaning Tower. So I am very grateful that I was able to use your phone line to contact your staff in English and arrange a swap to a large locker instead - just big enough for our two larger cases. So THANK YOU! - mission accomplished - we were able to spend an hour or so enjoying the Campo del Miracoll - eating our lunch, taking some photos - before retrieving our bags and boarding the PisaMover for the Airport. In case others make the same mistake though, perhaps make it clear that for hold luggage customers will definitely need a large locker!"

13/10/2019 - Leah G

"We used the facilities in Florence. The actual machine was down so we had to book online which caused some confusion. The options on the website are different than the options at the facility. Although the pictured show you can fit 3 rolling suitcases into the extra large locker along with a couple backpacks, we discovered you can only fit two rolling suitcases and one backpack per large locker. At the kiosk there is a call button for a taxi. When the call was finally answered, we were informed that they did not have any taxis available. We found one just outside. All in all, it saved us from having to cart our luggage around and we were very pleased with the location. I would definitely use these services again."

09/10/2019 - MINA CHAN

"The lockers are good size and it's worthwhile if you only need to stow your bags for 1-2 hours and also have a few small bags. If you have a big suitcase and need to stow it for longer period, you may want to check it in at a nearby hotel at 5 euro per piece per day. We like it that there's an 'open' locker (without doors) so we can check how many of our bags can fit inside. Good design and good system. The 'Stow Your Bags' lockers are easy to use, just follow the steps on the LED screen. However, what is really important is to enter your email correctly (and remember which email account you used) because the code to unlock to retrieve your luggage will be sent to your email. What was frustrating is that there was a customer who either didn't remember which email or perhaps she keyed in a wrong email address so she couldn't open her locker. She refused to let others to use the system while she kept trying (there's only 1 screen) and pressure those who was waiting for her to help. No one could except to ask her to check her email. We almost missed our train due to her holding up the system and having a queue built up!"

02/10/2019 - ELIZABETH STOEPPLER

"I was so happy to have found this while stopping in Milan. The location was only a little more than two minutes from the station but not far at all. It was easy to follow the instructions once we got started. My only complaints are the large box didn't seem as large as it said. I believe it said it could fit four bags, but we were only able to fit two carry on suitcases and a tote. Also, the locker assigned to us was located at a strange angle that made it very difficult to open and it locked before we could open it. So we had to enter our code to access the locker and then use real force to open it. Otherwise, it made it very easy and stress free to explore Milan for a few hours."

26/07/2019 - W. Sauer

"STOW YOUR BAGS was very convenient and easy to use. Caution: After looking at the measurements provided on line and measuring our biggest bag (19” x 30”), we thought our biggest bag would fit horizontally inside the biggest space. Our plan was to put other bags on top of the largest one. Unfortunately, it was maybe 1/2 “ wider and could not fit horizontally; so, we needed 2 storage units. However, we were in luck and very happy that 2 units were available! I’m rating it with a 4 star rating because although the lockers are secure and it is completely self automated; the front door locks at 11:00 pm (23:00). The restaurants had wait times and the service is relaxed in Italy. We ended our meal at 10:30 and could not stay to enjoy a little night life before retrieving our bags, because STOW YOUR BAGS was closing. A later closing time would be much nicer. We came into Milan by train. We did not have time to leave our bags at our hotel and still make it to our tour departure location on time; so, STOW YOUR BAGS was the perfect solution! Very close to the train station and very simple to figure out how to use! We would not have been able to enjoy a tour, of this facility was not available. Thank you for providing this much needed service!"

17/06/2019 - Ting Lim

"Very easy to use, just a few blocks from the station. We were able to fit 4 larger carry on bags and 1 smaller one in, although since some were a bit overstuffed, we had to be creative with our placement in the locker. We used this service in 3 different cities, very easy. One note of caution: Make sure to take the paper receipt when you first open your locker, since it has the unlock code so anyone could open your locker if you forget to take it. Also, when opening your locker, make sure to select that you are done with your reservation (there's 2 choices it asks you) because they don't know for sure that you finished your reservation on time otherwise."

01/04/2019 - SHELLY COHEN

"This was SO easy and convenient. We had a couple hours between checking out of the hotel and catching our train, and wanted to go see the Palazzo Massimo, near Termini station. Of course we couldn't do that with our luggage! Stow Your Bags was the perfect solution - just a couple blocks away from the museum. The only (small) problem was that we were assigned a top locker. I'm not very tall, and our bags were heavy. Fortunately, some kind folks who were also stowing their bags helped me hoist our luggage into the bin. (Getting them down is always much easier!) What a brilliant solution and so helpful to know about."

29/11/2018 - Meredith M.

"This was a GREAT experience! Very secure, and lockers fit my large suitcase, a backpacking backpack, and a tote easily. I felt safe leaving my luggage here for the day while we explored in Rome and it was very close to Roma Termini station where we were meeting back up again and leaving Rome. The only things I'd say could be improved were the cleanliness of the room - it had some trash piled up in various areas. it was also VERY difficult to find - of course, that may be normal in a foreign country where you don't speak the language or have wifi to navigate, but a sign sticking out into the street might be helpful. Loved the price as compared to the other options (other options were per piece of luggage or opened too late, or were for a set # of hours)"

18/10/2018 - CHRIS RUEFER

"A perfect option for our overnight trip to Venice. For us the location was only a 15 minute walk from our rental apartment and we had no difficulty finding it which says a lot in Venice! The process was easy and took only a minute or two (it's all self-service via a touch screen). A couple of suggestions if you use it - it may be better to book in advance as there aren't many lockers. Also, be aware that like some places in Europe, it requires a PIN with your credit card. We wound up using a debit card but as Americans, a PIN with a credit card still surprises us at times. I would definitely use this again if there is a location close enough to where we stay."

27/09/2018 - Sandra Murner

"Having this place close by to the Vatican was awesome, since we were coming from Sorrento area and our accommodations were close to the airport and with the lack of bus service, this was more convenient to just leave our bags in this locker space so we could partake in a tour and stay in that area for the day instead of lugging our suitcases around or wasting time getting to our accommodations and then returning back to this area. However, the little building that has these lockers were like 100 degrees inside that little room, we were sweating like crazy just putting our bags in there and the same when we were removing them. Other than that it was pretty easy to use and the lockers were very large size and we were surprised on that. Thanks for your services"

19/09/2018 - SASHAH HANDAL

"As the other reviews have said, it's a few blocks from Garibaldi Station but not a trek by any means. There is luggage storage provided by the station but at a higher cost. It's around the corner from THE BEST sfogliatelle in Napoli (Attanasio Sfogliatelle Cadli) so it definitely made it work the walk for us! The larger locker *does not* fit 4 large suit cases. It fits 3 carry-on sized suitcases at best. The inaccuracy of the description online was a bit frustrating but it was easy enough to rent another locker on site. The area may see a bit shoddy but the lockers were safe and under video surveillance, though I can't confirm whether the camera actually worked. Overall, great for what you pay for. Convenient enough and did the job while we required it! I would totally use this service again :)"

02/09/2018 - MARGARITA MANOLI

"We used Stow Your Bags in Rome near the Termini Station. When we contacted the staff prior our booking, we received an immediate and very helpful response. We decided to reserve our locker directly, the day before we would need it as we wanted to see the actual size of the lockers first. It turns out that they are exactly as advertised! We were very pleased with the size and procedures of booking a locker. It is safe, easily accessible and immediate. My advise would be to reserve a locker in advance, as they tend to sell out quickly. We were lucky to have booked the last one, when we arrived at the premises! Value for money and a worry-free trip :-)"

23/08/2018 - GINI BLOSTEIN

"Once we found the store, it was very convenient. We had to contact a customer service rep twice since we did not understand that we would be assigned a storage unit and had chosen one that fit our luggage and locked it. The rep was very helpful opening the unit electronically but we had to switch to 2 other units and pay for 2 units. They did not indicate that the first unit we used which fit our luggage was reserved or explain why we could not keep it. They did not say they did not have another unit big enough for our 2 pieces of carry on luggage available. However, it all worked out and we were impressed by the help and up to date information that the rep had in helping us navigate the system. The location near the train station was very convenient. Next time we might reserve a unit in advance."
